NOTICE

Sanitize It (Firefox Edition)
==============================

This Firefox edition is a derivative work based on the original "Sanitize It" 
browser extension created by Seth Cottle.

ORIGINAL WORK:
--------------
Project: Sanitize It
Author: Seth Cottle
Repository: https://github.com/sethcottle/sanitize-it
Copyright: (C) 2024 Seth Cottle
License: GNU General Public License v3.0 or later

The original work supports Chrome, Edge, and Safari browsers.

MODIFICATIONS FOR FIREFOX:
---------------------------
Modified by: Ryan Cuppernull
Copyright: (C) 2025 Ryan Cuppernull
License: GNU General Public License v3.0 or later (same as original)

Key modifications made for Firefox compatibility:
- Converted from Chrome API (`chrome.*`) to Firefox API (`browser.*`)
- Implemented background script clipboard access using document.execCommand()
- Replaced Chrome notification system with custom toast notifications
- Updated manifest.json for Firefox manifest v3 requirements
- Added browser_specific_settings for Gecko/Firefox compatibility
- Modified script injection to use Firefox-compatible parameters

ATTRIBUTION:
------------
Seth Cottle was inspired to create the original Sanitize It extension by 
Ryan Cuppernull (https://github.com/proxemics).

Ryan Cuppernull subsequently created this Firefox-compatible fork to bring 
the functionality to Firefox users.

